# Homepage Depth System Rules

## Zone Model
- Five zones defined in `apps/web/src/lib/depth-zones.ts`: epipelagic, mesopelagic, bathypelagic, abyssal, hadal.
- Sections declare their zone via `data-depth` attribute: `<section data-depth="mesopelagic">`.
- `HomepageDepthObserver` uses `IntersectionObserver` with hysteresis to set `html[data-home-depth]`.

## CSS Variable Architecture
- All depth-driven styling uses `--depth-*` variables defined in `globals.css` under `html[data-home-depth='<zone>']` blocks.
- Header: `--depth-header-bg`, `--depth-header-text`, `--depth-header-border`, `--depth-header-shadow`, `--depth-accent`.
- Surfaces: `--depth-surface`, `--depth-surface-strong`, `--depth-surface-border`, `--depth-surface-shadow`.
- Text: `--depth-text`, `--depth-text-muted`, `--depth-text-meta`.
- Interactive: `--depth-link`, `--depth-link-hover`, `--depth-button-bg`, `--depth-button-text`, `--depth-button-border`.
- Environment: `--depth-divider`, `--depth-glow`.
- Timing: `--depth-transition` (0.8s) and `--depth-ease` (cubic-bezier) for unified transitions.

## Design Principles
- Environment changes first, UI follows second.
- Transitions must be smooth and continuous — never abrupt zone snaps.
- Header backgrounds use flat `rgba()` colors (not gradients) so `background-color` can transition smoothly.
- `DepthBackground` layers (surface glow, light beams) attenuate with depth via opacity.
- A gradient dimmer overlay (`__gradient::after`) darkens the fixed gradient's upper viewport as depth increases.
- The footer must remain transparent and share the page's environmental background.
- Accent colors shift from warm teal (shallow) toward bioluminescent blue (deep).
- Lower-priority UI (dividers, metadata, eyebrow labels) transitions slightly slower than primary elements.

## Performance
- `IntersectionObserver` updates are batched via `requestAnimationFrame`.
- Hysteresis constant prevents rapid oscillation at section boundaries.
- `ScrollReveal` component uses `IntersectionObserver` with `unobserve` after reveal — no ongoing observation.
- Prefer CSS transitions over JavaScript animation for depth-linked visual changes.
